statements.sql: select * from `users` where `id` = 28 and `users`.`deleted_at` is null order by `id` desc limit 1
select * from `employees` where `user_id` = 28 and `employees`.`deleted_at` is null limit 1
select * from `point_settings` where `point_settings`.`deleted_at` is null order by `id` desc limit 1
select count(*) as aggregate from `employees` where `is_active` = 1 and `employees`.`deleted_at` is null

select DATE(time) as date, `employee_id`, MIN(time) as first_time, COUNT(*) as attendance_count from `attendances` where `employee_id` = 11 and year(`time`) = '2024' and `deleted_at` is null group by DATE(time)

select `holidays`.*, SUM(total_day) as total_day_sum from `holidays` where `holidays`.`start_date` >= '2024-01-01 00:00:00' and `holidays`.`end_date` <= '2024-12-07' and `holidays`.`deleted_at` is null limit 1

select `apply_leaves`.*, SUM(total_approved_day) as total_day_sum from `apply_leaves` where `apply_leaves`.`leave_approved_start_date` >= '2024-01-01 00:00:00' and `apply_leaves`.`leave_approved_end_date` <= '2024-12-07' and `apply_leaves`.`is_approved_by_manager` = 1 and `apply_leaves`.`is_approved` = 1 and `apply_leaves`.`employee_id` = 11 and `apply_leaves`.`deleted_at` is null limit 1
select * from `apply_leaves` where `employee_id` = 11 and `apply_leaves`.`deleted_at` is null order by `created_at` desc, `id` desc limit 3
select `id`, `employee_id`, `first_name`, `middle_name`, `last_name`, `email`, `position_id`, `department_id` from `employees` where `employees`.`id` in (11) and `employees`.`deleted_at` is null
select `id`, `position_name` from `positions` where `positions`.`id` in (2) and `positions`.`deleted_at` is null order by `id` desc
select * from `holidays` where year(`start_date`) = '2024' and `holidays`.`deleted_at` is null order by `start_date` desc, `id` desc

select `permissions`.*, `model_has_permissions`.`model_id` as `pivot_model_id`, `model_has_permissions`.`permission_id` as `pivot_permission_id`, `model_has_permissions`.`model_type` as `pivot_model_type` from `permissions` inner join `model_has_permissions` on `permissions`.`id` = `model_has_permissions`.`permission_id` where `model_has_permissions`.`model_id` = 28 and `model_has_permissions`.`model_type` = 'App\Models\User'

select `roles`.*, `model_has_roles`.`model_id` as `pivot_model_id`, `model_has_roles`.`role_id` as `pivot_role_id`, `model_has_roles`.`model_type` as `pivot_model_type` from `roles` inner join `model_has_roles` on `roles`.`id` = `model_has_roles`.`role_id` where `model_has_roles`.`model_id` in (28) and `model_has_roles`.`model_type` = 'App\Models\User'
